body: Fwiw I've been using int8 quantization for some time, and can confirm that it works with one single caveat that currently Relu doesn't properly handle symmetric int8 types. I'd been using my own Relu type since up until a few weeks ago ONNX didn't have int8 support in the relu schema, but I recently submitted a PR to them to add that.
@SilvanK4t1qbit , you're very welcome to make to PR and contribute. Thanks!

issue.title: Enable signed int8 data type for activations in static quantization

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**:
- Removes restriction to unsigned quantization data type for activations in `quantize_static`
- Makes symmetrization in quantization optional
- Preserves previous behavior if option is left unspecified 

**Motivation and Context**
Closes #6972

body: @yufenglee , I submitted a pull request for the features requested in this issue. Please let me know if you have any comments and suggestions!

issue.title: Add int8/int32 Relu for Opset 14

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: With opset14 we can now support Relu on int8 and int32 types. 

**Motivation and Context**
Use-case is running neural networks quantized to int8. This is a pre-requisite to supporting `int8` activations in the static quantizer (#6972).
